{
  "stem": "18102.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 144.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "In its way, the lesser of two evils was coming to take over Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Certainly, the Russians were preferable to the Nazis, but only in terms of the lesser of two evils.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "With the Russian army, however, came back all of those who had ran off before.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Every one of the city's hierarchy, the councilmen, the intellectuals, and so forth that had left in fear of the Germans returned, except two councilmen, my father and another gentleman, who did not trust the Russians any more than the Germans.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It is the-- that decision, among so many decisions that my father had to make that had to be absolutely right, to save our lives, and you couldn't make a mistake, was a critical decision in saving the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Because sure enough, within two days after all of these people returned, the NKVD, which is the precursor to the KGB, came to search for my father no differently than had the gestapo some weeks before.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Had my father returned, we would have been arrested and every one of those people that were arrested were sent off to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And most of them were never heard from again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "That was the lucky fate was to be sent off to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Who knows what else might have occurred.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But my father did not return.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "In fact, my mother and I didn't know where he was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "We heard nothing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And when his friends came to our house to-- to explain to my mother why my father didn't return, they said to her that he was a very stubborn man who didn't want to listen to good reason when others tried to tell him to come back with them.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
